# Hologram OS is a CONTENT-ADDRESSED substrate: a file's identity is the hash of its
# bytes (Law L5). Line endings are bytes, so they must be identical on every machine or
# the same source would derive a different κ. Normalize all text to LF in the repo AND in
# the working tree (eol=lf overrides core.autocrlf) so a clone on Windows, macOS or Linux
# hashes byte-for-byte the same — and matches the Pages/CI gate.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries: never touch. Git auto-detects most, but pin the formats this repo ships so a
# renormalize can never inject a CR or strip a byte. (.svg is XML — intentionally text.)
*.wasm   binary
*.wsz    binary
*.gguf   binary
*.exe    binary
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
*.webp   binary
*.woff   binary
*.woff2  binary
*.ttf    binary
*.otf    binary
*.eot    binary
*.wav    binary
*.mp3    binary
*.mp4    binary
*.webm   binary
*.ogg    binary
*.pdf    binary
*.zip    binary
*.gz     binary
*.jar    binary
